    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="430"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d430">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1364</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MIN1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 22, 1918</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received February 23, 12.37
                        a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1552. Swedish press reports via Petrograd’s telegram bureau. Council of People’s
                    Commissioners sent telegram to German Government, Berlin: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Council of People’s Commissioners hereby express protest against action
                            German troops against Russian Republic which had declared state of war
                            ended, and had begun demobilize Russian armies all fronts. They are
                            therefore constrained to consent to signing peace on conditions put
                            forward by delegations Central powers at Brest and announce reply to
                            terms specified by German Government will be given immediately.
                                <persName corresp="#p_LNVU1">Lenin</persName>, <persName
                                corresp="#p_TLDB1">Trotsky</persName>.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>…</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MIN1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
